<br>
Warrior Gear Selection: 101<br>
<br>
We are the most equipment dependent class in EQ.  We need more quality loots in our slots that any other class to do our job well.  Selecting gear is important since all our resources are limited, and therefore, trade-offs will have to be made.  This guide is intended to help warriors evaluate gear on their own, taking into consideration the situations in which the gear will be used, as well as the alternative uses for that equipment slot.<br>
<br>
There is a disturbingly large need in this (and most other class communities) to form a rigid dogma. People want a short set of immutable rules. X &gt; Y , A = B, D = useless, G = priceless.<br>
<br>
Some stats are meaningful (AC, hp, atk, regen, sta, runspeed, resists). Some stats are less meaningful (dex, agi, str). Some stats are irrelevant (int, wis, cha). ALL relevant stats have points of diminishing returns (or outright caps) that are relative to the situation.<br>
<br>
Testing and experience tell you when you have reached these points. Trying different set ups tells you more about the relative value of each item.<br>
<br>
The most important advice I can offer is this: dowload a parser, and do some testing.<br>
<br>
Do some thinking. Ask other people you respect about how they select their gear. Understanding the real tradeoffs helps you make much better decisions across a wider variety of situations than dogmatic adherence to some silly equations.<br>
